:"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-29/ch708/s203/e"},"text":"June 29, 1948, ch. 708, § 203(e)","children":[],"tail":" (30 words before proviso), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/1086"},"text":"62 Stat. 1086","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The words “basic pay * * * as the case may be” are inserted to conform to the terminology of the Career Compensation Act of 1949, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/802"},"text":"63 Stat. 802","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s231"},"text":"37 U.S.C. 231","children":[],"tail":" et seq.). The words “at the rate prescribed by law for his length of service”, in 10:1004, are omitted as covered by the words “base and longevity pay”. The words “base and longevity pay” are retained to cover the cases of members retired before the enactment of the Career Compensation Act of 1949, and advanced on the retired list after the enactment of that act. The words “and disregard a part of a year that is less than six months” are inserted to conform to footnote 4 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8991"},"text":"section 8991 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab6fd679-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1982 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This amends 10:8992 to correct an inadvertent error in the codification of title 10 in 1956 relating to retirement pay of warrant officers advanced on the retired list. For further details, see the explanation for amendment of 10:1405 made by section 1(17).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab6fd67a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idab6fd67b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 9362 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s9462"},"text":"section 9462 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab6fd67c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" inserted “or the Space Force” after “Air Force”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s806/b/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 806(b)(15)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8992"},"text":"section 8992 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s809/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 809(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 9344” for “section 8964”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section contained table with two formulas for recomputing retired pay of enlisted members and warrant officers of Air Force to reflect advancement on retired list."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348","children":[],"tail":" revised table generally by striking out provision in column 1 that for a person who first became a member of a uniformed service, as defined in section 1407(a)(2), after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-07"},"text":"Sept. 7, 1980","children":[],"tail":", one multiplier is the monthly retired pay base as computed under section 1407(e), substituting in formulas A and B provision that the retired pay base as computed under section 1406(e) or 1407 of this title be multiplied by the retired pay multiplier prescribed in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1409"},"text":"section 1409 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for the number of years credited for provisions that the monthly basic pay or base and longevity pay, as the case may be, subject to footnote 1, of the grade to which the member is advanced on the retired list be multiplied by 2½% of years of service credited, subject to footnote 2, and have subtracted from it the excess over 75% of pay upon which the computation is based, struck out footnote 1, which provided that the computation be at the rate applicable on the date of retirement, and redesignated footnote 2 as 1 and substituted “In determining retired pay multiplier” for “Before applying percentage factor” and “1/12” for “one-twelfth”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94/s923/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–94, § 923(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(I), in footnote 2 to table, substituted “Before applying percentage factor, credit each full month of service that is in addition to the number of full years of service creditable to the member as one-twelfth of a year and disregard any remaining fractional part of a month” for “Before applying percentage factor, credit a part of a year that is six months or more as a whole year, and disregard a part of a year that is less than six months”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94/s922/a/13"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–94, § 922(a)(13)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “The amount recomputed, if not a multiple of $1, shall be rounded to the next lower multiple of $1.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–295","children":[],"tail":" inserted “enlisted” before “member of the Air Force” and formula B relating to warrant officers."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513","children":[],"tail":" in heading for column 1 of table substituted “after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-07"},"text":"September 7, 1980","children":[],"tail":"” for “on or after the date of the enactment of the Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1981”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/342"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–342","children":[],"tail":" in heading for column 1 of table inserted provisions respecting applicability to persons after date of enactment of Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1981."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab6fd67d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab6fd67e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2018 Amendment","children